Title: Abnormal cisatracurium pharmacodynamics and pharmacokinetics among patients with severe aortic regurgitation during anesthetic induction.
Name: Atracurium besylate

Sentece: A conventional two-compartment PK model showed a higher plasma concentration of cisatracurium among the AR group with markedly reduced intercompartment transfer rate (K12 = 0.19 ± 0.02 and K21 = 0.11 ± 0.01 in the AR group vs. K12=0.26 ± 0.01 and K21 = 0.19 ± 0.01 in the control group, P < 0.01) compared to the control group.
Title: Abnormal cisatracurium pharmacodynamics and pharmacokinetics among patients with severe aortic regurgitation during anesthetic induction.
Name: Atracurium besylate
